<TITLE> Come soothing showers as Bay low makes landfall </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 22 (bdnews24.com) -- The depression triggered by the monsoon in the Bay drifted past Andhra coasts of India Friday noon, according to a weathercast. Dhaka and some other areas of the country experienced afternoon thundershowers, influenced by the passing depression. People felt relieved of the sultry weather. The meteorological department said monsoon winds strengthened due to the deepening of the low in the Bay, which may cause gusty to squally winds blowing over seaports. Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla seaports were asked to keep local cautionary signal No. 3 until further notice. The river ports have been told to hoist cautionary signal number 1. The skies over Dhaka and adjoining areas were cloudy since noon. Dhaka had 18mm rainfall from noon to 6pm. Bogra had the highest rainfall of 51mm in the day. The highest temperature of the country was recorded at Maijdee Court at 37 degrees Celsius. The capital had the highest temperature at 32.7 degree Celsius. The weathercast said most of the areas of Barisal and Khulna divisions and some areas of the remaining four divisions might experience light to moderate rainfall. Some places might see moderate to heavy rainfall. All fishing trawlers and boats in the north Bay were advised to stay near the coast and operate with caution. bdnews24.com/mr
